import React from 'react'
import { Col, Container, Image, Row } from 'react-bootstrap'

const UserHero = () => {
   const user = {id: 6, nickname: 'Superman', real_name: 'Clark Kent', img: 'https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/marvel_dc/images/a/a5/Superman_Vol_5_1_Textless.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20180711061148'}

    return (
        <Container className="mt-3">
            <Col md={4}>
                <Image width={300} height={300} src={user.img}/>
            </Col>
            <Col md={4}>
            <Row></Row>

            </Col>
            <Col md={4}>
            <Image width={300} height={300} src={user.img}/>

            </Col>
            <Col md={4}>

            </Col>
        </Container>
    )
}

export default UserHero
